OL,3,CJohnny Mercer may face jail sentence
OL,4,Cfor withholding names
OL,6,FGiving his reason for not disclosing
OL,7,Fthe names during his evidence in
OL,8,FFebruary, Mr Mercer told counsel to
OL,9,Fthe inquiry Oliver Glasgow KC: "The
OL,10,Fone thing you can hold on to is your
OL,11,Fintegrity and I will be doing that
OL,12,Fwith these individuals."
OL,14,FIn a previous order compelling the ex-
OL,15,FConservative MP for Plymouth to hand
OL,16,Fover the names, the inquiry chairman
OL,17,Fsaid the consequences of failing to
OL,18,Fcomply without reasonable excuse would
OL,19,Fbe "a criminal offence punishable with
OL,20,Fimprisonment and/or a fine".
