OL,3,CJohnny Mercer may face jail sentence
OL,4,Cfor withholding names
OL,6,FMr Mercer then submitted an
OL,7,Fapplication to the probe on 3 April,
OL,8,Fin which he argued he was either
OL,9,Funable to comply with the order, or it
OL,10,Fwas not reasonable for him to comply
OL,11,Fwith it.
OL,13,FIn his statement on 11 July following
OL,14,Fthe ruling, which he posted on X, Mr
OL,15,FMercer said: "I note the statement
OL,16,Ffrom the inquiry chair, containing as
OL,17,Fit does multiple factual inaccuracies
OL,18,Fand assertions.
OL,26,@wD@NOU
