OL,3,CJohnny Mercer may face jail sentence
OL,4,Cfor withholding names
OL,6,F"I have given my statement to the
OL,7,Finquiry. Mr Haddon-Cave must now stop
OL,8,Ffixating on attempting to bully me, I
OL,9,Fhave done nothing wrong. I gave my
OL,10,Fword to junior personnel who
OL,11,Fapproached me. I intend to keep it."
OL,13,FIn his ruling on, Sir Charles said:
OL,14,F"The applicant submits that he is a
OL,15,Fprotector of whistleblowers.
OL,17,F"He chose publicly, however, to
OL,18,Fdisclose that friends told him about
OL,19,Fallegations of unlawful killings by
OL,20,F(special forces) in Afghanistan.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@dO]vD@AOUyD@AOU|D@Apm|D@Ppn
