OL,3,CJohnny Mercer may face jail sentence
OL,4,Cfor withholding names
OL,6,FAn inquiry spokesperson said: "Mr
OL,7,FMercer is refusing to disclose
OL,8,Finformation which may be important to
OL,9,Fa public inquiry which is seeking to
OL,10,Festablish the truth about grave
OL,11,Fallegations of multiple murder
OL,12,Finvolving UK Special Forces.
OL,14,F"Mr Mercer accepts the inquiry has
OL,15,Fsecure measures in place to protect
OL,16,Fthe names and identities of his
OL,17,Fsources and that witnesses coming
OL,18,Fforward to the inquiry have protection
OL,19,Ffrom risk of prosecution for breaches
OL,20,Fof the Official Secrets Act or for
OL,21,Ffailure to report misconduct.
OL,26,@nD@_OUvD@AOU
